# ssf-product-pm Cursor Rule

When the user asks for product design outputs, PRD, feature specs, UI specs, prototype prompts, UI annotations, or product baseline/change documents, follow the repository Skill at:

- `SKILL.md`
- `templates/`
- `references/`

Rules:

1. Do not generate traditional backlog management, priority matrices, MVP roadmaps, or next-phase plans unless explicitly requested.
2. Before writing files, read `ssf-workspace/index.md` when it exists and resolve the target instance; do not overwrite unrelated instances.
3. Merge project description, field/user research, market research, and competitive analysis into one research insight document.
4. Generate requirement analysis before PRD.
5. Use PRD only for product-level context.
6. Use feature task specs as the main execution unit for architecture AI, coding AI, and testing AI.
7. Every feature task must keep the same full structure; write "none / TBD" instead of omitting sections.
8. Keep UI IA, structured UI interaction spec, and prototype prompt + UI annotation as separate documents connected by IDs.
9. Treat structured UI specs and UI annotations as the source of truth, not prototype images alone.
10. Use product baseline and change spec for all change scenarios.
11. Follow `references/id-conventions.md` and `references/quality-checklist.md`.
